## 🔹 7. Real QA Test Cases for Role APIs

Test login as User

```
/features → dashboard only
/enumerator → 403
/devices → limited
/config → 403
```

Test login as FSE

```
/features → enumerator present
/enumerator → 200
/devices → full
/config → 403
```

Test login as Admin

```
/features → all
/enumerator → 200
/devices → all
/config → 200
```

This is real automation scenario.

---

## 🔹 8. Why Role Testing is critical in Healthcare

Because:

* Only engineer can connect device
* Only admin can change config
* Only medic can view patient
* Only service can open enumerator

Wrong permission = serious issue.

So role API testing mandatory.

---

## 🔹 9. How automation will test roles (later)

Flow:

```
Login as role
Get token
Call API
Check response
```

Python example:

```python
token = login("FSE")

headers = {
    "Authorization": f"Bearer {token}"
}

response = requests.get("/features", headers=headers)

assert "enumerator" in response.json()["features"]
```

We will do this later step-by-step.

